  <summary>1/6/1999--Introduced.
Taxpayer Fairness Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow the following as deductions: (1) the Federal Insurance Contributions Act and the Railroad Retirement Tax Act (RRTA) taxes on employees; (2) 50 percent of the tax on self-employment income; and (3) 50 percent of the RRTA tax on employee representatives.</summary>
